       fhir:definition [ fhir:v "A language which may be used to communicate with the related person about the patient's health." ] ;
       fhir:comment [ fhir:v "If no language is specified, this *implies* that the default local language is spoken.  If you need to convey proficiency for multiple modes, then you need multiple RelatedPerson.Communication associations.   If the RelatedPerson does not speak the default local language, then the Interpreter Required Standard can be used to explicitly declare that an interpreter is required." ] ;
       fhir:requirements [ fhir:v "If a related person does not speak the local language, interpreters may be required, so languages spoken and proficiency is an important things to keep track of both for patient and other persons of interest." ] ;
